# API & middleware conventions

## Routing

- Register routes via `middleware.Router` (`RegisterAPI`) and apply via `Router.Apply(mux)`.
- Use explicit HTTP methods (`http.MethodGet`, etc). Empty method means “allow all”.

## Middleware ordering

- Keep “context enrichment” early (e.g., `ClientMiddleware` before others).
- Avoid per-request heavy allocations inside middleware; build handler chains upfront when possible.

## Responses

- For API errors, return consistent JSON error payloads using `api.Error(...)` and the existing JSON writer helpers.
- Use correct status codes (`401` auth, `403` forbidden, `405` method, `429` rate limit, `500` unexpected).

## Safety

- Never trust client input; validate query/body fields in controllers before calling services.
- Avoid leaking internal error details to clients; log server-side, return sanitized messages.
